# Repo Workflow Guardrails

- Never commit directly on `main`.
- Never push directly to `main`.
- Never force-push to `main`.
- Never bypass git hooks with `--no-verify`.
- Before making commits, create a task branch from latest `main`.
- Open PRs for all shared changes.
- Keep each PR focused on one concern/task.
- If user asks to commit/push while on `main`, ask whether to create a branch first and only proceed on `main` as an explicit exception.

